==Transportation==
{{Map|1275,3160|1354,3109|1237,3042|mtype=pin|mapID=0|align=right|caption=Gemstone crab locations in Tlati rainforest}}
[[Children of the Sun]] must first be completed to access [[Varlamore]].

After partial completion of [[Twilight's Promise]], the [[Quetzal Transport System|quetzal transport system]] will become accessible to players. The [[Civitas illa Fortis Teleport]] or [[Perfected_quetzal_whistle|quetzal whistle]] can be used to reach the quetzal transport system quickly, which can be used to fly to [[Tal Teklan]] to reach the [[Tlati Rainforest]] for the first time. From there, run south to the crab nest. Each gemstone crab nest has a cave that leads to the location of the fight, or the next respawn location if between fights. If there is no crab at the location you arrive at, simply use the cave to reach the correct area. After each fight, this is also used to reach the next crab respawn point. 

Other methods to reach the gemstone crab include:
* A charged [[Pendant of ates]] can be used to teleport just north of [[Kastori]] after activating the [[Statue of Ates]] located there. From here, the player can run north to reach the eastern gemstone crab site.
* The Quetzal landing site that must be built at [[Kastori]], which is about the same distance to the eastern crab nest as the Tel Teklan quetzal is to the southern crab nest.
** The [[Hunter cape]] teleport to the [[Hunter's guild]] is also next to a [[Quetzal Transport System|Quetzal]] landing site
* [[Fairy rings|Fairy ring]] code {{Fairycode|ais}} to [[Auburn Valley]]. From here, the player can run south west to [[Achilka]], who can take them to both Tal Teklan or Kastori, with both boat endpoints being close to gem crab nests to their north.
* If lacking any of the methods above, walking from Civitas illa Fortis to the [[Quetzacalli Gorge]] is safe and there is a [[Mountain Guide (Auburn Valley)|mountain guide]] who will take you to [[Nemus Retreat]]. From there you can walk south to Achilka and take her boat.

==Strategy==

Unlike most monsters, the crab does not die. It has effectively infinite health and remains in its nest for 10 minutes before burrowing. As a result, fighting it serves as an [[afk activities|idle training method]], allowing players to gain combat experience with minimal interaction and little to no downtime.

Almost any equipment can be used effectively, and players of all levels can participate. The crab has no defensive stats, and uses a melee attack that can only hit for 1 damage to players it is facing. Strength bonus should be prioritised to maximise experience gain.

Players may wish to consider using low level prayers like [[Burst of Strength]] which will always increase max hit, while draining prayer extremely slowly. 

Although reduced by 12.5%, experience rates at the crab are still generally favourable, especially for mid level and higher level players. [[Melee]] is the most effective combat style when training against the gemstone crab. [[Ranged]] training may be worthwhile at the crab at lower levels, especially before unlocking better methods such as [[Pay-to-play_Ranged_training#Levels_45–99:_Chinning_maniacal_monkeys|chinchompas]]. [[Magic]] isn't recommended, as it is inefficient at all levels. A low level player is recommended to read the [[Gemstone Crab/Strategies#Magic|section on magic]] further down the page for more information.

The gemstone crab does not count as a crab for the sake of [[Slayer task/Crabs|slayer tasks]], and so the [[slayer helmet (i)]] provides no benefit here.

==Equipment==
When selecting gear, the primary consideration is maximizing [[Damage_per_second/Melee|damage]] to increase experience gain. The crab's minimal defensive stats and high health make nearly all weapons viable for consideration; players are able to use whatever their best weapon is already. As the boss is intended to be fought AFK, not all recommendations are required to be followed if the player does not wish to afford the extra effort to use them, such as special attacks or the use (and upkeep) of Prayers; however they are still listed here if one wishes to use them.

Generally, the tabs in the following sections are ordered from least to most effective; or lowest requirements to highest.
===Melee===

<tabber>
Lower Level=
For lower levelled players, some of the other armour sets may be too expensive, or not yet able to be equipped due to current levels or quest progression. The main stat to prioritise is still Strength bonus, although at a lower level not as many items exist for increasing it. Wearing [[Prayer bonus]] gear like [[Monk's robes]] is best if you are unable to get anything else for that slot, if planning to use offensive prayers like [[Burst of Strength]] or [[Ultimate Strength]]. Prioritise your budget towards the most effective weapon first, as it will have the largest effect on your damage. Most weapons will work, although it is recommended to use faster weapons like [[scimitar]]s or [[sword]]s.</br> At very low combat levels(under 30s), weapons like the [[goblin paint cannon]] can still perform well due to their faster attack speed. It's also worth noting that Colossal blade has unique way of damage calculation and because of this, Colossal blade outperforms even Abyssal whip until your strength level is around 75-80.

