Dharok's=

[[Dharok's equipment]] can provide the best damage output, but requires the player to remain at very low [[Hitpoints]]. It is recommended to have at least level 90 or more Hitpoints to gain the full effect of the armour set, as with less than this blood moon or obsidian armour sets are likely to be more damage, although it is best to calculate with your own gear and levels. To maximise the effect of the armour, the player should remain between 2-4 Hitpoints for the whole encounter, although players with 99 Hitpoints can still maintain higher damage than other sets while only resetting their Hitpoints between each crab fight. You can prevent Hitpoints from regenerating by turning on and off the [[Rapid Heal]] prayer at least once per minute, and damage yourself down with the use of any item that can deal [[Hitpoints#Self-inflicted_damage|damage to yourself]], namely the [[locator orb]] or [[dwarven rock cake]]. 
</br>
While not often, the gemstone crab '''can deal lethal damage''', so do not drain your Hitpoints all the way to 1. It is good to take some food that heals a small amount multiple times, such as [[cooked giant crab meat]], [[guthix rest]], or [[Cabbages|sacks of vegetables]], in order to restore Hitpoints in case of accidentally draining them to 1, or getting hit down from 2. Just like the obsidian armour set, due to the Dharok's set boosting damage by a percentage, [[Strength bonus]] gear in the remaining slots is especially potent for boosting damage output.
