Obsidian=
The obsidian set is a solid choice that can match up to max gear. The strategy centres around combining [[obsidian armour]], the [[berserker necklace]] and the [[Toktz-xil-ak]]. These items synergise to grant the player a set bonus, which increases damage output by 30%. The base damage for this set is relatively low, due to its low strength bonus. It therefore relies on other boosts to increase damage output; its 30% damage increase allows other strength boosts to scale much better. With other boosts, such as [[Ultimate Strength]]/[[Piety]] and [[super strength potion]]s, the damage output can rival that of much more expensive gear sets. The accuracy penalty is negligible when fighting the gemstone crab, as it has no defensive stats.
</br>
The void armour set also performs quite well, and can be paired with any weapon, rather than just obsidian weaponry (see the "Lower levelled" tab for more). It scales similarly with strength boosting gear in the remaining slots, and so is placed here for clarity.
</br>
This setup does not consume charges, unlike with [[Blood moon armour]] and [[Dharok's equipment]]. This can save a considerable amount of gp, as blood moon costs {{nocoins|100000}} per hour to use, and dharok's costs {{nocoins|22000}} per hour, assuming that one repairs using an NPC such as [[Bob]].
