Fighting the gemstone crab does not require any items, although some may be brought to increase damage dealt at the cost of reducing AFK time:
* [[Super strength]] potions, or [[Strength potion]]s. [[Black warlock mix]]es can also be used, and will share the Strength buff to other nearby players, but have low trade volume. Several [[black warlock]]s spawn to the east of the southern and northern crab nests, and south of the eastern nest; with 55 [[Hunter]] they can be caught before initiating combat with the crab to boost [[Strength]].
* Bring a method to reach the crab, such as a [[Pendant of ates]], [[quetzal whistle]], or runes for [[Civitas illa Fortis Teleport]]. Banking can be done in Tal Teklan, so holding onto it isn't necessary.
* (Optional) [[Prayer]] restoring items such as [[prayer potion]]s if using offensive prayers to increase damage. [[Moonlight moth mix]]es can be used to restore your own Prayer and that of 3 other nearby players fighting the crab, and at lower levels can provide more Prayer restoration than potions. If fighting the crab with a group of [[Friends List|friends]], or multiple of your own accounts, the moths can be coordinated to maximise their effectiveness across the recipients of the restoration.
** If using prayer potions, bring a [[Holy wrench]] or other items which share its effect.
** If only using the lowest tier of Prayers, it can be more efficient to just restore Prayer at the [[altar]] in Tal Teklan, as it would only need to be done every 5-10 crabs.
** Using the Ancient Mace special attack can restore low amounts of prayer, negating the need for prayer restoring items.
* (Optional) A [[special attack]] weapon, such as the [[dragon claws]] or [[dragon dagger]] to use up special attack energy for bonus damage.
** A [[defender]] will be beneficial if using a two-handed main weapon with a one-handed special attack weapon. Ideally a [[dragon defender|dragon]] or [[Avernic defender]].
** If looking to conserve supplies or not worry about using special attacks frequently, using a [[Dragon battleaxe]] special attack at the start of each new crab fight can replace the need for Strength potions.
* (Optional) A [[pickaxe]], to mine the boss after defeat and loot gems.
** A [[Gem bag]] may be brought to hold additional gems, or simply a [[chisel]] to cut them for [[Crafting]] experience and then dropped or [[High Level Alchemy|alched]].

===Ranged===
<tabber>

Low level=
Due to the crab's low defence, ranged accuracy is not very impactful, and faster weapons like [[dart]]s and [[throwing knives]] excel here. However, when the [[adamant crossbow]] is unlocked at 46 Ranged, it is strongly recommended to consider using it with [[ruby bolts (e)]] due to the passive effect which allows players to hit up to 60 on the crab at the cost of some of their current hitpoints. Although this can never kill the player, it is recommended to keep distance from the crab to avoid taking damage from it also. Bringing some food just in case and using [[Rapid heal]] can also offset the damage taken.
</br></br>
For those that have access to the wooden [[Blowpipe|blowpipes]], using them with the highest tier darts that they can fire (Mithril with [[Camphor blowpipe|Camphor]]; Adamant with [[Ironwood blowpipe|Ironwood]] or [[Rosewood blowpipe|Rosewood]]) will provide some additional ranged accuracy and strength in exchange for giving up the off-hand slot. This will result in higher DPS if you do not have access to a ranged off-hand with higher offensive stats than the blowpipe. Using [[Rune darts]] without a blowpipe will yield higher DPS for a higher cost.
</br></br>
The usefulness of offensive prayers will vary depending on the specific weapon used, and the Ranged level you are currently at, as whether a max hit is gained from activating prayers is not consistent until higher levels, unlike melee. If using a standard [[Ranging potion]], it will usually be worthwhile to have [[Sharp eye]] or [[Hawk eye]] enabled, as while the buff decays over time you will pass over some level thresholds where the prayers increase damage.

