===Magic===
The reduction in experience at the gemstone crab along with the lack of an [[elemental weakness]] means that the experience and cost-efficiency is not as good as other options. For example, [[Frost Crab]]s have a 100% weakness to [[fire spells]], and allow the player to [[idle]] for 10 minutes at a time with a quick reset in between (the same as the gemstone crab). [[Rock Crab]]s are also available with a 20% earth weakness, for those without completion of [[The Heart of Darkness]], and are otherwise nearly identical.

Generally, [[Magic]] is much faster and more cost-efficient to train on other monsters or with utility spells, since the gemstone crab has a negative experience multiplier, and does not possess an [[elemental weakness]]. One method of magic training that is recommended to be done at the gemstone crab for more active players is to weave in spellcasts while efficiently training one of the other combat styles.

[[High Level Alchemy]] is the most accessible spell, and can be cast in between hits. This does take a lot of effort, but can be done without losing any ticks. As an example, alching noted [[yew longbows]] profits {{Coins|768-({{GEP|Fire rune|5}}+{{GEP|Nature rune|1}}+{{GEPrice|Yew longbow}})}}gp per cast, granting the player an additional {{Coins|(768-({{GEP|Fire rune|5}}+{{GEP|Nature rune|1}}+{{GEPrice|Yew longbow}}))*500}}gp per hour along with {{NoCoins|65*500}} magic experience per hour. This can be done with a large [[RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Alchemy|variety of items]], for variable profit.

The spell [[Telekinetic Grab]] can also be cast at most times as long as the player is not an [[Ironman]]. There is usually a pretty consistent stack of dropped ammunition under the boss from lower level players shooting it without a fully upgraded [[ava's device]]. This can result in upwards of about 125k experience per hour on sufficiently populated worlds that are uncontested for picking up the ammo. Additionally one can profit from the resulting ammo picked up. If using the Eclipse atlatl method with a melee strength boosting cape instead of an ava's device, this can be done on your own ammunition to not need to rely on other players.

Alternatively, the player can cast [[magic imbue]] on the Lunar spellbook. This can give passive magic experience at a cost of {{Currency|Coins|{{GEP|Fire rune|7}}+{{GEP|Fire rune|7}}+{{GEPrice|Astral rune|2}}}} per cast. Magic imbue costs the player {{Currency|Coins|({{GEP|Fire rune|7}}+{{GEP|Fire rune|7}}+{{GEPrice|Astral rune|2}})/86}}gp/xp. The spell, granting 86 experience every 12.6 seconds, adds an additional {{NoCoins|86*100}} magic experience per hour to the player's total experience, and requires half as many clicks as the previous spells per cast, and is cast less often.

If fighting the gemstone crab is still preferred, the following methods and equipment are recommended:

